				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for <mono>join</mono> calls is:
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px; margin-bottom:50px">
<mono>f++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline" style="margin-bottom:-40px">
join{options}(object, string)
join{options}(object, string, begin)
join{options}(object, string, begin, end)
</pre>
</div><br>
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px; margin-bottom:50px">
<mono>n++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline" style="margin-bottom:-40px">
\@join{options}(object, string)
\@join{options}(object, string, begin)
\@join{options}(object, string, begin, end)
</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					The <mono>join</mono> function takes all items in an iterable object and returns them joined in to one string, it takes 2-4 input paramters, the first parameter should be an iterable object, the second parameter should be a string to separate each item with, the optional third parameter should be a non-negative integer to specify which position to begin at and the optional fourth parameter should be a non-negative integer to specify which position to end at.
				</p>

				<h4 id="options">
					Options
				</h4>
				<p>
					The following options are available for <mono>join</mono> calls:

					<center class="table">
						<table id="join_options_table" class="alt">
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>option</th>
									<th>description</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tr>
								<td><mono>@ent(<)-</mono></td>
								<td>add separator at beginning</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><mono>-@ent(>)</mono></td>
								<td>add separator at end</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><mono>@ent(<)-@ent(>)</mono></td>
								<td>add separator at both beginning and end</td>
							</tr>
							<tfoot>
								<tr>
									<th>option</th>
									<th>description</th>
								</tr>
							</tfoot>
						</table>
					</center>
				</p>

				<h4 id="f++-eg">
					f++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Examples of <mono>join</mono> being used with <mono>f++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
function(exampleFunc)
{
	console("params: {", join(params, "; "), "}")
}

exampleFunc("cat", dog, "%")</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="n++-eg">
					n++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>join</mono> being used with <mono>n++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
\@function(exampleFunc)
{
	\@console("params: {", \@join(params, "; "), "}")
}

\@exampleFunc("cat", dog, "%")</pre>
</div>
				</p>
			</div>
